The paper deals with the decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes in question are expander codes, which are a type of graph-based code, so the paper could also be relevant to the subfield of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the properties of the Tanner graph, which is a common tool in coding theory and could be relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the expansion properties of the code, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and could also be relevant to the subfield of social networks and network analysis (cs.SI).
